==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: alpha particle
<hw>alpha particle</hw>. <fld>(Physics & Chem.)</fld> <def>a particle
emitted at high velocity from certain radioactive substances. It is
identical to the helium nucleus, consisting of two protons and two
neutrons. Rays of such particles are called <er>alpha
rays</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Alpha rays</ent>⟦br⟧
